[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Deliver Forecasts and Reorder Points to DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The forecast artifact in S3 is the immutable record; the DynamoDB table is the operational view. Materials-management dashboards and the ERP integration query DynamoDB by `facility_sku_id` to get the current forecast and reorder point at low latency. The loader writes two records per SKU: a CURRENT record at a stable composite key the operational consumers query, plus a versioned history record so prior forecasts remain queryable for audit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def load_forecasts_to_dynamodb(records: list) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Step 5: write the forecast records to DynamoDB. The
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "current" table receives one record per
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     facility_sku_id, overwriting any prior CURRENT record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     on idempotent re-run. The "history" table receives a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     versioned record keyed on (facility_sku_id, generated_at).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns counters for the per-pipeline metrics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_table = dynamodb.Table(SKU_FORECAST_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     history_table = dynamodb.Table(SKU_FORECAST_HISTORY_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     counts = defaultdict(int)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The boto3 resource client's batch_writer auto-batches
