[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "Python companion correctly initializes boto3 clients (s3, dynamodb resource, events, glue, sagemaker, stepfunctions, cloudwatch) with adaptive retry Config, and uses correct API call signatures: s3.put_object(Bucket/Key/Body/ContentType), eventbridge put_events with Entries[Source/DetailType/Detail/EventBusName], cloudwatch put_metric_data(Namespace/MetricData), dynamodb resource Table().batch_writer() context manager with put_item, glue start_job_run(JobName/Arguments), and stepfunctions start_execution. Error handling is present via try/except wrappers in [3memit[23mevent and [3mput[23mmetric plus extensive inline comments explaining failure modes, retry behavior, DynamoDB Decimal/NaN/Inf rejection, and graceful degradation paths. The recipe pattern is demonstrated end-to-end across all five steps (consumption prep, ADI/CV² segmentation with procedure-driven override, per-segment model training with backtesting, forecast generation with reorder-point/EOQ math, and DynamoDB current+history loading) and is wired into run_forecast_pipeline with a runnable run_demo entrypoint. Forecasting models (Holt-Winters, Croston, Syntetos-Boylan, procedure-driven, cold-start, trailing-mean) are fully implemented with real math rather than stubs; mock infrastructure is intentional and clearly documented as demo substitution for real boto3 clients, with the real clients constructed first."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h